<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="inspiration-n">inspiration <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /ˌɪnspə'reɪʃn/    美 /ˌɪnspə'reɪʃn/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-u-c">1.★ <strong>[U] 灵感；[C][常用单数]启发灵感的人 / 事物； 鼓舞人心的人 / 事物：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Genius is one percent inspiration and ninety-nine percent perspiration.
天才就是1%的灵感加上99%的汗水。</p><footer>——爱迪生</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He gave me the inspiration to pick up my pen again.
他鼓舞我重新拿起笔（写作）。</p><footer>2015 江苏改</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Many poets <strong>drew / took their inspiration from</strong> the nature.
许多诗人从大自然中获得灵感。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Jennifer is a first-generation graduate and an <strong>inspiration to</strong> her family.
詹尼弗是第一代毕业生，这对她的家人是个鼓舞。</p><footer>2020山东</footer></div></div>